SIMPLE: greatly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Greatly
<hw>Great"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a great degree;
much.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will <qex>greatly</qex> multiply thy sorrow.</q> <rj><qau>Gen.
iii. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nobly; illustriously; magnanimously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By a high fate thou <qex>greatly</qex> didst expire.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>great-nephew</ent>⟦br⟧
